attributes.magic: POSIX shell script, ASCII text executable

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The script begins by identifying and terminating various running processes, including those commonly associated with cryptocurrency mining or other system compromise. Concurrently, it systematically removes numerous files and directories across the file system that are linked to these processes or other specific paths. Following this cleanup, the script attempts to download a remote file from a hardcoded IP address (http://87.121.84.24/nuts/poop). It makes multiple attempts to save this downloaded content under the name "lrt" into different system directories. For each successful download, it grants execute permissions to the file and then executes it in the background.
